Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer* role with *Tailscale*. I bring over three years of professional experience building production-grade distributed backend systems and AI-powered services, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered systems that directly reflect the distributed systems depth, observability rigor, and security-first mindset this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I built a robust observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks across a distributed system of 1,000+ backend service endpoints — enabling proactive incident response and maintaining stability under production load. I designed and delivered a secure MCP AI interaction layer applying a security-first approach, where every natural-language intent was translated into safe, validated tool calls with rigorous input validation and API contract enforcement. I also architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph for scalable coordination across distributed systems workflows, and applied KV-cache optimizations that reduced end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50%. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform on AWS with a security-first mindset, and designed a scalable cloud-agnostic Storage Service in Python with PostgreSQL and Redis handling secure file operations and networking across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO — directly building the kind of reliable, multi-environment backend infrastructure Tailscale's product depends on.

My work at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab sharpened both my distributed systems instincts and my ability to communicate complex technical ideas clearly — skills central to Tailscale's fully remote, asynchronous culture. I managed the full lifecycle of model training and inference across Pace University's HPC cluster, diagnosing and resolving complex issues to ensure high availability in a distributed environment. I also led workshops on GPU programming and AI Agent construction for 50+ students, requiring me to break down complex systems clearly in writing and speech — exactly the kind of strong written and verbal communication skills Tailscale values. Outside of my professional work, I built Dark Factory, an open-source CLI orchestrator that demonstrates my security-first design instincts through PTY-based command interception and uses Y-crdt for distributed state synchronization across machines, broadcasting real-time updates to maintain stability without polling.

I have long been passionate about making networks easy, sensible, and safe, and Tailscale's mission to build the new Internet — small, private, secure, distributed networks that just work — is exactly the kind of problem I want to dedicate my engineering to. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

